ht mix. Many of the albums end with a story track, read by famous English performers including [[Benedict Cumberbatch]],<ref>{{ cite news | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/yo-sherlock-benedict-cumberbatch-performs-spokenword-with-friendly-fires-8269621.html | title = Yo, Sherlock! Benedict Cumberbatch performs spoken-word with Friendly Fires | work = The Independent | accessdate = 19 February 2013 | location = London | first = Alice | last = Jones | date = 31 October 2012 }}</ref> [[Will Self]], [[Brian Blessed]] and [[Patrick Moore]]. With the exception of [[Jamiroquai]], [[Air (band)|Air]] and [[Bill Brewster (DJ)|Bill Brewster]]'s contributions, each release includes a cover version recorded by the artist(s).\n\nThe series has been met with critical acclaim,<ref>{{ cite news | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/reviews/album-midlake-late-night-tales-late-night-tales-2259628.html | title = Album: Midlake, Late Night Tales (Late Night Tales) | work = The Independent | accessdate = 19 February 2013 | location = London | first = Andy | last = Gill | date = 1 April 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{ cite web | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/wmb6 | title = MGMT Late Night Tales Review | publisher = BBC Music | accessdate = 19 February 2013 }}</ref> with [[GQ]] Magazine praising ''Late Night Tales'' as \"The Rolls Royce of compilations\".<ref>GQ Magazine, 2010</ref> 2011 saw the label celebrate their 10th anniversary with a box set including all albums to date.<ref>{{ cite web | url = http://www.clashmusic.com/news/late-night-tales-celebrate-10th-anniversary | title = Late Night Tales Celebrate 10th Anniversary | work = Clash | accessdate = 19 February 2013 }}</ref> [[Friendly Fires]]' compilation<ref>{{ cite web | url = http://www.residentadvisor.net/news.aspx?id=17641 | title = Friendly Fires tell Late Night Tales | publisher = Resident Advisor | accessdate = 19 February 2013 }}</ref> released in November 2012 marked the 30th in the series.\n\n== Albums ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!align=\"left\" width=\"650\"|Album information\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Another Late Night: Fila Brazillia]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Fila Brazillia]]\n*Released: 19 February 2001\n*Cat no: ALNCD01\n*Singles: \"[[Nature Boy]]\" ([[Nat King Cole]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Another Late Night: Howie B]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Howie B]]\n*Released: 24 July 2001\n*Cat no: ALNCD02\n*Singles: \"[[Under the Boardwalk]]\" ([[The Shadows|The Drifters]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Another Late Night: Rae & Christian]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Rae & Christian]]\n*Released: 1 March 2001\n*Cat no: ALNCD03\n*Singles: \"[[Flash Light (song)|Flashlight]]\" ([[Parliament (band)|Parliament]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Another Late Night: Zero 7]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Zero 7]]\n*Released: 18 February 2002\n*Cat no: ALNCD04\n*Singles: \"Truths and Rights\" ([[Johnny Osbourne]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[AnotherLateNight: Groove Armada|Another Late Night: Groove Armada]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Groove Armada]]\n*Released: 3 June 2002\n*Cat no: ALNCD05\n*Singles: \"[[Fly Me to the Moon]]\" ([[Frank Sinatra]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Another Late Night: Tommy Guerrero]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Tommy Guerrero]]\n*Released: 23 September 2002\n*Cat no: ALNCD06\n*Singles: \"[[Come Together]]\" ([[The Beatles]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Another Late Night: Kid Loco]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Kid Loco]]\n*Released: 10 February 2003\n*Cat no: ALNCD07\n*Singles: \"Paralysed\" ([[Gang of Four (band)|Gang of Four]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Late Night Tales: Nightmares on Wax]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Nightmares on Wax]]\n*Released: 12 May 2003\n*Cat no: ALNCD08\n*Singles: \"Brothers on the Slide\" ([[Cymande]] cover version)\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''''[[Late Night Tales: Sly & Robbie]]'''''\n*Artist: [[Sly and Robbie|Sly & Robbie]]\n*Released: 14 July 2003\n*Cat 