ion Mars rover |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-11386_3-57557184-76/nasa-announces-plans-for-new-$1.5-billion-mars-rover/ |newspaper=[[CNET]] |date=December 4, 2012 |first=William |last=Harwood |quote=Using spare parts and mission plans developed for NASA's ''Curiosity'' Mars rover, the space agency says it can build and launch a new rover in 2020 and stay within current budget guidelines. |accessdate=December 5, 2012}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NAA-20130312\">{{cite web |last=Bosco |first=Cassandro |title=NASA/JPL Mars Curiosity Project Team Receive 2012 Robert J. Collier Trophy |url=http://naa.aero/siteadmin/data/document/Collier%202012%20PR.pdf |date=March 12, 2013 |work=[[National Aeronautic Association]] |accessdate=February 9, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223025521/http://naa.aero/siteadmin/data/document/Collier%202012%20PR.pdf |archivedate=February 23, 2014}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"PHYS-20120815\">{{cite web |url=http://phys.org/news/2012-08-degree-street-view-mars.html |title=A 360-degree 'street view' from Mars |work=[[PhysOrg]] |first=John |last=Williams |date=August 15, 2012 |accessdate=August 16, 2012}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"CuriosityRover-360Cities\">{{cite web |url=http://www.360pano.eu/show/?id=731 |title=Mars Panorama - Curiosity rover: Martian solar day 2 |work=360Cities |first=Andrew |last=Bodrov |date=September 14, 2012 |accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"msl-where\">{{cite journal |url=http://mars.nasa.gov/msl/mission/whereistherovernow/ |title=Where is Curiosity? |journal=Space Science Reviews |volume=170 |issue=1\u20134 |page=401 |accessdate=January 1, 2020|last1=Mahaffy |first1=Paul R. |last2=Webster |first2=Christopher R. |last3=Cabane |first3=Michel |last4=Conrad |first4=Pamela G. |last5=Coll |first5=Patrice |last6=Atreya |first6=Sushil K. |last7=Arvey |first7=Robert |last8=Barciniak |first8=Michael |last9=Benna |first9=Mehdi |last10=Bleacher |first10=Lora |last11=Brinckerhoff |first11=William B. |last12